HEADWORD: Aam
<hw>Aam</hw> <pr>(⟦add⟧m <it>or</it> ⟦aum⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[D. <ets>aam</ets>, fr. LL. <ets>ama</ets>; cf. L. <ets>hama</ets>
a water bucket, Gr. <?/]</ety> <def>A Dutch and German measure of
liquids, varying in different cities, being at Amsterdam about 41 wine
gallons, at Antwerp 36⟦frac12⟧, at Hamburg 38⟦frac14⟧.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Aum</asp> and <asp>Awm</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

